    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const articles = $input.all().map((item, i) => {\n  const title = item.json.title || 'Untitled';\n  const link = item.json.link || '';\n  const raw = item.json.contentSnippet || item.json.content || item.json.summary || '';\n  const snippet = raw.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').trim().substring(0, 200);\n  return `${i+1}. ${title}\\n   URL: ${link}${snippet ? '\\n   ' + snippet + '...' : ''}`;\n}).join('\\n\\n');\nreturn [{ json: { articlesText: articles } }];"
      },
      "id": "node-19",
      "name": "Format for AI",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [2500, 815]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert financial analyst and options trading strategist. Here are today's latest market news articles:\n\n{{ $json.articlesText }}\n\nCreate a pre-market Discord briefing for an options trader. Use this exact format:\n\n**Market Sentiment:** (bullish/bearish/neutral and why in 1 sentence)\n\n**Top Catalysts Today:**\n(list 2-3 key events: earnings, Fed, economic data, geopolitical)\n\n**Sectors to Watch:**\n(which sectors are moving and why)\n\n**Stocks in Play:**\n(2-3 stocks with news that could cause big price movement - ideal for options)\n\n**Risk Factors:**\n(1-2 things that could cause unexpected volatility)\n\n*Not financial advice. Do your own research.*\n\nUse Discord markdown. Keep under 1800 characters total."
      },
